title: For Sale:  Highly Customized Ruger LCP .380
postcontent: Customized Ruger 380 LCP - The pistol is has been highly customized for CCW. One of the issues I had when I acquired the LCP was the low profile sites that were almost non functional for the accuracy that the LCP was capable of delivering so I had the slide dovetailed and fitted for better profile sights including a front tritium night sight. This is something Ruger decided to deliver with the new LC 380 pistol except that the new pistol is significantly heavier, nearly twice the weight. In addition, the feeding ramp has been highly polished to increase reliability and the trigger/sear has been polished for smooth trigger pull. This offering includes the original manuals, three magazines, case, and all that came with the original purchase. The gun has 300-500 rounds through it to break it in for reliability and I have fired a broad range of ammo without any malfunction. After the break-in and ramp polishing, this been absolutely reliable. For the buyer, I would have suggestions for ammo as I do considerable ballistic testing and have done that with this particular gun. The gun is also fitted with a Crimson trace laser and the gun is sighted dead on with both night sights and the CT laser for 30 feet combat distance. I have also fitted the gun with a belt clip and a home-made trigger block safety of my own making for IWB carry. The trigger block safety I crafted is easy to activate, you just push it out to the left or right as you place your finger on the trigger, yet adds a level of security to enable carrying a round in the chamber. I got the idea for a product I saw for glocks. I have carried this gun for nearly a year and it disappears; you don't feel it at all in your WB. I have also used a pocket holster and it disappears in your pocket. It is incredibly light for a .380; a great summer carry gun. This gun is capable for excellent accuracy for its size, shooting 2-3" groups at 7 yards in fast fire mode for me. The offering comes with the original box, documents, locks, soft case, etc. It also comes with a book hide out I created which holds the gun and two magazines with a dust jacket for a book called 'Forgotten Valor' - see photos. It also comes with 3 each of extra different weight Wolf recoil and firing pin springs. I have trusted this gun with my life. You can buy a new LCP for less money, but you won't get the customizations or reliability out of the box you will with this one. Will accept cash or PayPal. Not interested in trades.

Don't let the "Duty" designation trick you. The P-07 model is a compact handgun -- just as appropriate for concealed carry as it is for uniformed duty. The abbreviated 3.8" barrel and compact grip allow the Duty to disappear under clothing much more easily than full-sized models. This compact size and polymer frame along with the new slide profile (fully machined from bar stock) reduce weight, making the P-07 Duty a great choice for concealed carry. Easily adaptable to low light use, the Duty features an accessory rail to which a light or laser can be attached.

When designing the polymer frame for the Duty, the decision was made to retain the basic grip shape (circumference, angle, etc.) so popular in the CZ 75 family of handguns. The polymer frame platform eliminated the need for the grip panels that are used on most steel and alloy-framed autos. The absence of the grips resulted in some available space that was used to increase the magazine capacity by 2 rounds. The results speak for themselves -- the flush-fitting magazine of the P-07 Duty holds the same number of rounds that the full-sized versions of the CZ 75 do in both 9mm and .40 S&W.

The most innovative feature of the P-07 duty is the Omega trigger system. The new mechanism was first introduced on the P-07 model. It simplifies the CZ 75 trigger system, uses fewer parts and improves the trigger pull, but the real story is in the versatility it provides for its owner. The Omega system allows users to choose between operating the handgun with a decocking lever (installed) or a manual safety (included) by a simple parts change.
